OL,3,CThree more arrests after arson attack
OL,4,Con Jewish community ambulances
OL,6,FFour ambulances from Hatzola, a
OL,7,Fvolunteer-led ambulance service
OL,8,Foperating in the Golders Green area of
OL,9,Fnorth-west London, were set on fire in
OL,10,Fthe early hours of March 23, causing
OL,11,Fgas canisters stored in the vehicles
OL,12,Fto explode.
OL,14,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer called
OL,15,Ffor communities to "all stand
OL,16,Ftogether" in the face of the "horrific
OL,17,Fantisemitic attack", while Chief Rabbi
OL,18,FEphraim Mirvis said the targeting of
OL,19,Fthe volunteer service was
OL,20,F"particularly sickening".
